featureType.name: CERF_NHill_FEI_Openness
featureType.title: CERF - Fetch-based exposure indices for temperate Australia - Openness
featureType.abstract: These data describe quantitative exposure indices generated using cartographic fetch methods on a 0.01 degree grid across temperate Australia (South Australia, Victoria and Tasmania). This layer describes openness. Openness is a measure of the distance of a site to the nearest coastline in all directions and describes potential exposure to locally generated seas and undefined swell.
